  "kiddushin": [
   {
    "text": "The first step of Jewish marriage is called ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "erusin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " or ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ". After ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ", the woman is designated to the man for marriage and would need a halachic divorce in order to remarry. However, the couple is not yet married, and may not live together or have physical contact. The first Mishnah of ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "Maseches Kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " discusses the different ways in which a man and woman can produce a state of ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ". ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "Kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " is sometimes translated as \"engagement\" although the binding nature of ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " is one difference between it and ordinary engagement.",
    "type": "text"
   }
  ],
  "nisuyin": [
   {
    "text": "The second step of Jewish marriage is called ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "nisuyin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ". After ",
