    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ", the couple must create a state of ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "nisuyin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " in order to be formally married. In the times of the Gemara ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "nisuyin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " might be done a year after ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": ". Today, however, ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "kiddushin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " and ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "nisuyin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " are done in the same wedding ceremony. Typically ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "nisuyin",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " is done by having the wife enter the residence of the groom, either his actual residence, or more commonly the ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "chupah",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " or ",
    "type": "text"
   },
   {
    "type": "italics",
    "tokens": [
     {
      "text": "yichud",
      "type": "text"
     }
    ]
   },
   {
    "text": " room.",
    "type": "text"
   }
